  "prompt": "Why does Apple not put a Flashlight on the iPad?",
  "response": "Actually, Apple does provide a built-in Flashlight/Torch feature on iPads running iPadOS, just like on iPhones. You can access it by:\n\n1. Swiping down from the top-right corner to open Control Center\n2. Tapping the Flashlight icon\n\nHowever, the traditional LED flashlight is typically less bright on iPads compared to iPhones because iPad cameras generally have smaller LED flash units. For most practical purposes, using an iPad as a flashlight isn't as effective as using a smartphone.\n\nIf you're having trouble finding the Flashlight feature, make sure your iPad is running a recent version of iPadOS and that the Flashlight control is enabled in Control Center settings.",
